-- U.S. Portfolio Holdings of Foreign Securities Grew 16.1% in 2012
-- B y   K a s i a   K l i m a s i n s k a
-- 2013-10-31T20:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-31/u-s-portfolio-holdings-of-foreign-securities-grew-16-1-in-2012.html
U.S. portfolio holdings of foreign
securities rose 16.1 percent at the end of 2012 from a year
earlier, with the largest investments made in debt and equities
from the U.K., Canada, Cayman Islands and Japan.  Total holdings were $7.94 trillion on Dec. 31, 2012,
compared with $6.84 trillion at the end of 2011, according to
the data released by the Treasury Department in Washington
today.  The survey is taken by the Treasury, the  Federal Reserve 
and the  New York  Fed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kasia Klimasinska in Washington at 
 kklimasinska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
